The paper discusses bibliometric measures and proposes a new variant of the h-index that takes into account an individual's impact on the research community. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and social and economic systems (cs.SOC). However, given the focus on bibliometrics and impact, cs.DL and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
